  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA201-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu kaḻaṟiya pāṅkaṟkut talaimakaṉ uraittatu (EV: colliyatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what HE said to the charioteer who reproached [him].</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA201">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            malaiyuṟai kuṟavaṉ kātaṉ maṭamakaḷ</l>
<l>            peṟalaruṅ kuraiya ḷaruṅkaṭik kāppiṉaḷ</l>
<l>            colletir koḷḷā ḷiṉaiya ḷaṉaiyō</l>
<l>            ḷuḷḷal kūṭā teṉṟōy maṟṟuñ</l>
<l>            cevvērp palaviṉ payaṅkeḻu kollit </l>
<l>            teyvaṅ kākkun tītutīr neṭuṅkōṭ</l>
<l>            ṭavveḷ ḷaruvik kuṭavarai yakattuk</l>
<l>            kālporu tiṭippiṉuṅ kataḻuṟai kaṭukiṉu</l>
<l>            murumuṭaṉ ṟeṟiyiṉu mūṟupala tōṉṟiṉum</l>
<l>            perunilan kiḷariṉun tirunala vuruviṉ </l>
<l>            māyā viyaṟkaip pāvai pōlap</l>
<l>            pōtalol lāḷeṉ ṉeñcat tāḷē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The beloved [and] inexperienced daughter of the Kuṟavaṉ</l>
<l rend="indent4">staying in the mountains,</l>
<l>she [is] difficult to obtain, she [is] guarded by severe protection,</l>
<l>she does not receive words – such is she.<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">iṉaiyaḷ aṉaiyōḷ</term>: my proposal is to take the first, <term xml:lang="ta">iṉaiyaḷ</term>, as a subject on which the attributes mentioned so far depend as appositions, while the second, <term xml:lang="ta">aṉaiyōḷ</term>, is a predicate noun summing up: all that can be said of her.</note></l>
<l>*Thinking of her is not appropriate* is what you said,<note place="foot">Perhaps the <term xml:lang="ta">maṟṟu</term> singles out the speech of the confidante. I cannot, however, make sense of the um here.</note></l>
<l>– of her who [is] in my heart [and] does not consent to going away,</l>
<l rend="indent2">just as the illusionary image</l>
<l rend="indent2">in a beautiful form more brilliant than the lustre of the vast ground(?),</l>
<l rend="indent">even if the wind dashes [and] roars, even if the hasty drops are rushing,</l>
<l rend="indent">even if thunder claps furiously(?), even if obstacles appear in number,</l>
<l rend="indent3">within the western mountain with pretty white waterfalls,</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the long peak free from evil, that the god guards,</l>
<l rend="indent4">on Kolli, fertile as a red-rooted jack-tree.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
